properties.description: Grade I Victorian Gothic church by G E Street, architect of the Royal Courts of Justice. The recent conservation project reveals the majestic colours of Daniel Bell's painted ceiling, plus Dow Jones Architects' contemporary heritage wing.
properties.name: Grand Junction at St Mary Magdalene Church, Paddington

properties.description: The independent cultural centre Pushkin House will contribute to this year's Open House Festival through a programme of events and community initiatives at its Grade-II listed building in Bloomsbury Square.
properties.name: Pushkin House

properties.description: The Small Beer Brewery was founded in 2017 by James Grundy and  Felix James. It is the first of its kind, specialising in brewing world class beer at a sociable strength.
properties.name: Small Beer Brewery

properties.description: Alton Estate is renowned for its mix of high-rise Le Corbusian architecture in Alton West & its low-rise Scandinavian approach to modernism in Alton East. Designed by the London County Council  architects they completed in 1959.
properties.name: Alton Estate

properties.description: The four-story Church façade and prominent seven-story tower is covered in Portland stone and highlighted by a golden steeple. The interior features the Christus statue and a large mural of the resurrected Jesus Christ.
properties.name: Hyde Park Chapel

properties.description: This is a community-driven development fulfilling the burgeoning demand for urban renting. With bespoke dwellings, onsite team and amenities to meet a variety of needs, it’s not just a home but a complete hub of urban activity.
properties.name: Apo Kew Bridge

properties.description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
properties.name: Fore Street Art Trail

properties.description: A community-run evening of talks and discussions on the future development of Convoys Wharf. The historically important 40 acre site is slated for a controversial large-scale re-development. A must for all concerned about London's future.
properties.name: Public Meeting: Time for Change: A New Vision for Convoys Wharf

properties.description: A Grade II listed motor garage and petrol station built in the style of a Japanese pagoda in 1928. Now a Tesco Express.
properties.name: "Chinese" Garage

properties.description: Altab Ali Park was renamed in 1998 after a murdered 25-year-old Bangladeshi Sylheti clothing worker. Formerly known as St. Mary's Park, it is the site of the old 14 C white church, St. Mary Matfelon which gave Whitechapel its name.
properties.name: Altab Ali Park

properties.description: This short tour will take you through Westminster station, a brutalist dream and one of the most beloved stations on the Underground network. We will discuss the station's architecture and how it has been modified since reopening in 1999.
properties.name: Westminster station tours

properties.description: For thousands of years witches of all form have walked the isles of Britain and been the topic of folklore and history. On this tour led by Vincent Edward Manda from Wonders of London we discover more about the witches of London.
properties.name: Witches & Witchcraft History Tour
